Goal
To produce a complete, durable engineering plan and task breakdown for implementing a new feature. The output is a file-based plan using a consistent template that persists across working sessions and can be incrementally updated.

Output Location
Directory: .cursor/rules/features/

Filename: <feature-name>.mdc — One file per distinct feature.

Never overwrite or extend another feature file unless the new work is a direct continuation of that same incomplete feature.

Initial Workflow
Receive Prompt – User describes a feature or functionality to implement.

Ask Clarifying Questions – Ensure understanding of goals, flows, scope, data, tech constraints, etc.

Generate Initial Plan – Output a new file in .cursor/rules/features/<feature-name>.mdc using the template below.

Pause for User Feedback – Do not start work until the user reviews and confirms the plan is solid.

Enter Execution Loop – Once approved, implement tasks in order, updating the file between steps.

The task plan should specifically call out the files that need to be updated and the tests that need to be written. When updating existing code, the task plan should also call out the existing tests that need to be updated. And the actual code patterns/functions that need to be updated. Be specific.

