Work Loop
After the feature file is created and confirmed:

Implement next task

Add/update corresponding test case as specified in task description

Run the test plan to verify correctness and avoid regressions

Commit code once task and tests are verified

Update .mdc file with completed checkboxes or new notes

Repeat until all tasks complete

Testing Requirements
Each task implementation must include a corresponding test case that validates the specific functionality being added or modified.

Tests should cover both positive cases (feature works as expected) and negative cases (feature handles errors gracefully).

For bug fixes, tests should reproduce the original bug and verify the fix prevents regression.

For new features, tests should validate the feature works in isolation and integrates properly with existing functionality.